Hello,
I use the the kernel 2.2.15 with IPv6 support (not as modul).
At the Linuxbox is a tunnelbroker running that creates and deletes
ipv6 tunnelinterfaces (I use the iptunnel tool from net-tools
for that).
Problem:
After some days all Interfaces lost the ipv6 addresses. I can
not add the address again.
ifconfig if_name add <ipv6_address>
reports no error and ifconfig if_name shows:
if_name       Link encap:IPv6-in-IPv4  
              UP POINTOPOINT RUNNING NOARP  MTU:1480  Metric:1
              RX packets:320 errors:0 dropped:0 overruns:0 frame:0
              TX packets:388 errors:0 dropped:0 overruns:0 carrier:0
              collisions:0 txqueuelen:0 
Any Ideas ?
Thank you
Uwe
